with all sections the other phases need.\\n- **test-writer.md**: Prerequisites, Step 4, and summary line updated to reference `AGENT.md`. Fallback instruction (\\\"search external docs, update AGENT.md\\\") is good.\\n- **implementer.md**: Steps 2, 3, 10 reference one-pager. Standing instruction before Step 4 is well-placed. All \\\"research report\\\" references replaced.\\n- **SKILL.md**: Phase descriptions accurately describe the one-pager handoff.\\n\\n### Issues Found\\n\\n7 concrete issues, roughly ordered by severity:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Issues to Fix\\n\\n### 1. `implementer.md` Step 3 references nonexistent `config.go`\\n\\n**File:** `implementer.md:47`\\n**Problem:** Says \\\"Add the agent to the config map in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/config.go`\\\" — this file doesn't exist. Agent wiring uses blank imports in `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`.\\n**Fix:** Replace with: \\\"Ensure the blank import `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG\\\"` exists in `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`\\\"\\n\\n### 2. `researcher.md` Phase 4 asks for info the researcher can't produce\\n\\n**File:** `researcher.md:67`\\n**Problem:** Phase 4 says \\\"Field coverage: which `Event` struct fields can be populated per event\\\" — but the researcher was told NOT to read `event.go` where `Event` struct fields are defined. The researcher can't assess field coverage without knowing the struct.\\n**Fix:** Remove the \\\"Field coverage\\\" bullet from Phase 4. The implementer handles field mapping when reading `event.go`.\\n\\n### 3. One-pager template missing \\\"Static Checks\\\" section\\n\\n**File:** `researcher.md:81-122`\\n**Problem:** Phase 2 runs 7 static checks (binary, help, version, hook keywords, session keywords, config dir, docs). These results aren't captured in the one-pager template. The verdict (COMPATIBLE/PARTIAL/INCOMPATIBLE) depends on these checks, but there's no place to record the detailed results.\\n**Fix:** Add a `## Static Checks` section to the template between `## Verdict` and `## Binary`:\\n```markdown\\n## Static Checks\\n| Check | Result | Notes |\\n|-------|--------|-------|\\n| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n| ... | ... | ... |\\n```\\n\\n### 4. `implementer.md` Step 13 partially redundant with Step 3\\n\\n**File:** `implementer.md:227-231`\\n**Problem:** Step 13 says \\\"Register hook commands: Search `cmd/entire/cli/` for where hook subcommands are registered and add the new agent\\\" — but Step 3 already says to wire up blank imports in `hooks_cmd.go`. Step 13 also says \\\"Verify registration: The `init()` function...\\\" which Step 3 also covers.\\n**Fix:** Simplify Step 13 to just verification: \\\"Verify registration by running `mise run test:ci`. The `init()` in `${AGENT_SLUG}.go` and blank import in `hooks_cmd.go` (from Step 3) should be sufficient.\\\"\\n\\n### 5. `test-writer.md` Step 1 reads 8 files — no priority guidance\\n\\n**File:** `test-writer.md:12-23`\\n**Problem:** Step 1 lists 8 infrastructure files to read. This is a lot of context to load. The most critical files for writing a new agent runner are `agent.go` (interface) and one existing agent (e.g., `claude.go`), not all 8.\\n**Fix:** Add a note: \\\"**Most critical:** Focus on items 3 (`agent.go` — the interface you must implement) and read one existing agent implementation (e.g., `e2e/agents/claude.go`) as a reference. Skim the rest for context.\\\"\\n\\n### 6. One-pager template doesn't list valid EventType values\\n\\n**File:** `researcher.md:95-99`\\n**Problem:** The hook mapping table has an \\\"Entire EventType\\\" column, but the researcher needs to know the valid values. They learned them from `agent-guide.md` in Phase 1, but by Phase 5 they need to recall them. A reference list would prevent incorrect mappings.\\n**Fix:** Add a comment after the table: \\\"Valid Entire EventTypes: `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\\"\\n\\n### 7. `SKILL.md` doesn't mention AGENT.md lifecycle\\n\\n**File:** `SKILL.md:36-62`\\n**Problem:** The one-pager is created by Phase 1 and consumed by Phases 2 and 3, but SKILL.md doesn't explicitly state that Phases 2/3 may update it. The implementer.md has the standing instruction, but the orchestration doc should also note this.\\n**Fix:** Add a brief note after Phase 3: \\\"**Note:** `AGENT.md` is a living document — Phases 2 and 3 update it when they discover new information during testing.\\\"\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n1. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/researcher.md`** — Issues #2, #3, #6\\n2. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/test-writer.md`** — Issue #5\\n3. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`** — Issues #1, #4\\n4. **`.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md`** — Issue #7\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter applying fixes:\\n1. Grep for `config.go` — should not appear in any skill file\\n2. Grep for `Field coverage` — should not appear in researcher.md\\n3. Read researcher.md one-pager template — should have Static Checks section and EventType reference\\n4. Read implementer.md Step 13 — should be verification-only, not re-registration\\n5. Read test-writer.md Step 1 — should have priority note\\n6. Read SKILL.md — should mention AGENT.md lifecycle after Phase 3\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-kiro-oneshot/46c073e8-9109-4faf-bd0b-fe9c0209ac96.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"ca0d913b-2606-44bd-85ff-0776e386b112\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T01:12:32.380Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Audit: Agent Integration Skills (Post One-Pager Refactor)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe one-pager refactor was just implemented. This audit reviews the changes for correctness and identifies further improvements — bugs, inconsistencies, and structural issues across all four sk